profile_positions.description:
- Donor portfolio: EU/EC, Erasmus+, Nuffic, NORAD, GIZ, SIDA, GAC, USAID and other institutional funding;
- Creating consortiums with international strategic partners in the Netherlands and other EU countries, 
   and with local strategic partners in 28 countries we are active in; 
- developing a business portfolio as an income generation between universities (research and applied sciences) and LF. Aim: developing LF as a knowledge broker in the areas of child and youth disability, inclusive disability in health and education.
- Scouting calls for proposals from different donor and informing colleagues accordingly.
- Developing proposals, reviewing proposals.
- Developing engagement strategies with European Foundations and Trustes
- Developing engagement strategies with international/institutional donors.
- Mapping International Family and Corporate Foundations, Trustees and Philanthropies; 
- Mapping Insitutional Donors and Global and Local Strategic Partners;
- Partnering with donors to support disabled children and youth in the Global South;
